The paper deals with arrangements of circles and their intersection graphs, which are topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The study of graphs and their properties is also relevant to computer science theory (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of recognizing a subclass of penny graphs, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
